=left class=m><span class=title> Unmentioned Sullon issue: newbie loot</span><hr size=1> The loot in the areas I was hunting (and I tried A LOT of places out of desperation) was so pathetically nerfed I ended up deleting the char so I could quickly create other newbies to verify if its like that in other newbie zones. So far the best I've found is Paineel and 2nd Innothule, but even those are really bad.<br>
<br>
Anyone found a low level zone that still has decent loot on Sullon, even 1/10 of what it was 2 years ago?  Haven't rolled up an Iksar yet, will check FoB next. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugrinkle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grinkle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/14/01 8:11:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=326.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Unmentioned Sullon issue: newbie loot</span><hr size=1> Are you saying it is nerfed compared to Blue servers today, or nerfed compared to you recollection of what it was like in newbie zones two years ago? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/14/01 8:46:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=326.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.theglobe.com/Kambic/TRINITY.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Unmentioned Sullon issue: newbie loot</span><hr size=1> I'm not sure, me and a friend were camping the snake in BB a few levels ago, and the drop rate on GSF's seemed about 1 fang per 8 snakes. That seems like a lot worse ratio then back when I hunted them on Canbik... which I think was about 1 in 3.<br>
<br>
On Wisp there seem to be a lot more beetles and things. Back when I hunted there on Canbik, I used to hunt the snakes a lot (poison glands, fangs, etc. sold to merchant good)... over the course of 3 levels now, I've seen, yes, one snake. That's it. And I've seen no more then five vampire bats, they used to be quite common when I hunted them (wondering if they did this because they were very easy to farm wings off of - usually 4 or 5 wings per drop LOL). These last two I am certain of, it is not simply my memory serving me improperly, especially because I've only seen ONE snake ;p<br>
<br>
 <p><a href="http://pub70.ezboard.com/bscreamspvp"><img src="http://members.theglobe.com/kambic/sig/joyous.gif"></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umajestykvz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MajestykVZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/14/01 9:01:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=326.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.armstrongsupply.com/images/bigtwink.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Unmentioned Sullon issue: newbie loot</span><hr size=1> I hadn't noticed it to a great degree.  I assumed that my memory of drop rates as a true newbie may seem to have been shorter, when I was still exploring the world and it was all new to me as opposed to being a veteran player scampering to aquire gear and get thru the lowbie levels. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uugliitchybottom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ugli Itchybottom</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/14/01 9:28:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=326.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Unmentioned Sullon issue: newbie loot</span><hr size=1> In 9 levels I got 2 worn great staves and saw ZERO cracked staves on any MOB in any zone.  In fact only 1 in 20 or so decaying skellies has any weapon at all, where it used to be 1 in 2 or 1 in 3.  The weapons they do have are almost exclusively rusty dagger, rusty short sword, rusty bastard sword, and rusty axe (the ones that sell for 6silver 7 copper or less).<br>
<br>
Coin loot is GONE off skellies, orcs, + kobolds in most zones.  Not lowered.  GONE.  Only exception I found was skels and frogs in Innothule have about 2sp each now.<br>
<br>
6gp shields used to be fairly common on mummies and orc raiders in N Ro.  This time I have seen *ONE*.  Their weapons and cloth drops are also almost gone.<br>
<br>
WIth other chars I have had full cloth by level 3 or 4 by killing orcs.  In 9 levels I saw about 10 pieces drop on Sullon, half of them duplicates of what I had.<br>
<br>
Fire beetle eyes used to average about 1.75 per beetle (once in awhile 1 had just 1 or you find a really rare one with 3).  Now about 1 in 5 has AN eye, most have NONE, except in Paineel, where the fire beetles are how they used to be.  Spiderlings that used to average 2 silks each now have about 1 silk in 3 spiderlings.<br>
<br>
Bone chips, bat wings, etc., have become exceedingly rare compared to how they dropped 2 years ago, across all zones I checked.<br>
<br>
I've made a lot of chars over the last 2 years, and the loot seemed to get progressively worse each time, BUT, not so severe as this where its blatantly obvious.  So I kind of suspect if you create a char on a blue server now it will be crappy like Sullon. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uugliitchybottom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ugli Itchybottom</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0> at: 6/14/01 10:06:19 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulirintz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lirin TZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/14/01 1:18:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=326.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Unmentioned Sullon issue: newbie loot</span><hr size=1> paineel and the warrens are still gold i know.  as much as a month ago me and a friend started newbies there, SK and necro, she has all her spells at level nine, i have full ringmail and banded and all spells.  plus about 90 stacks of bonechips in the bank for when we go to the mainland. <p>Soapy <br>

Warrior of the Tribunal <br>

Anarchy

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uugliitchybottom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ugli Itchybottom</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/14/01 1:28:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=326.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Unmentioned Sullon issue: newbie loot</span><hr size=1> Paineel no longer has *ANY* coin loot. (It was one of the places I checked).  However, the skeletons there still drop weapons at a reasonable rate (unlike FP and gfay areas), and the kobolds still drop containers (again, unlike orcs etc.), plus paineel has the only unnerfed fire beetles.  Bone chips and bat wings have gotten rare there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugruggdamighty.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GruggDaMighty</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/14/01 8:48:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=326.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Unmentioned Sullon issue: newbie loot</span><hr size=1> Bring on the nerfs!! w00t! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uugliitchybottom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ugli Itchybottom</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/14/01 9:17:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=326.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Unmentioned Sullon issue: newbie loot</span><hr size=1> I logged in my old druid char and cleared out some newbie areas on Bristlebane.  Seems the lack of loot is Sullon specific.  Most beetles on BB had 2 eyes, skeletons and orcs had silver + copper  (not as much as I remember, but still...), more of them popped with weapons and orcs dropped lots of cloth.<br>
<br>
So to answer Grinkle's question:  Sullon loot is severely nerfed compared to blue servers today.<br>
<br>
I wonder if they are trying to encourage us to bank then run around trying to PK as this will be the only way to afford even basic spells, equip, etc (and will most likely be insufficient).<br>
<br>
The vampire pet thing Kambic mentions is even more petty than it looks (when you think about people auctioning to buy batwings every once in awhile).... not like batwings are actually valuable.  They are sold in infinite quantities in every shaman guild and most mage guilds for 1sp (with good CHA). <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uugliitchybottom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ugli Itchybottom</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0> at: 6/14/01 9:45:23 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umaximilean.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maximilean</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/17/01 4:40:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=326.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> loot</span><hr size=1> On VZ and Zeb, Greater Faydark now has orcs that drop CB belts, rather than just the orcs in CB dropping them.  This was implemented some months ago, I think.  <br>
<br>
There will be no (or not much) twinking market on SZ, so this won't help as much for cash, but it'll get some leather and xp for those who can take the orcs... It'll get ambitious WE druids some of the first leather around, I suspect.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uugliitchybottom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ugli Itchybottom</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/17/01 5:22:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=326.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: loot</span><hr size=1> Killed dozens of orcs in gfay on SZ before heading to Freeport.  Not one belt dropped.  The most cash any had was 2 copper.  (most had no cash at all).   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/17/01 1:09:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=326.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.theglobe.com/Kambic/TRINITY.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: loot</span><hr size=1> Well I've seen a few more bats and snakes there, but they are still rather uncommon IMO. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showPrevMessage?topicID=326.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showNextMessage?topicID=326.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=326.topic&index=11><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/repl